description:
Bedlam's iconic Tectonic, to set off tremors in boardroom or bar, as worn by the Very Rev Larry Love (aka Rob lead singer of Alabama 3, providers of "The Sopranos" theme song) and other pillar / terrors of society.

Made from that staple of Savile Row, J & J Minnis grey flannel chalk stripe, it is cut on the bias, technically tricky and using many more metres than a straightforward cut.

£2400 made to measure three-piece;

As worn by Nile Rodgers (pictured with Lady C), the #1 Hit-Meister Up-All-Nighter Daft Punkster Legendary Funkster. They didn't name the band "Chic" for no reason, the man knows how to dress;

As worn by Goldie (pictured with Lady C), snappy dresser, flashy gnashers;

As worn by Paul Oakenfold, DJ superstar du monde au studio.
100% viscose SO WASH COOL as silk.
